; device-heartbeat.form — a body broadcasts presence on any channel; others pick it up and connect.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-09):
;   "Use wifi, bluetooth, even audio (speaker/mic), video (screen/camera) to share on any available
;    channel, and broadcast heartbeats for other devices to pick up and connect — and the same on the
;    Mac — running in a way I can SEE what it is doing, what state it is in, which organs are active,
;    surprise events, infer error (core for learning)."
;
; TWO things, lane-sorted: a heartbeat/discovery BODY (this recipe), and observability (a carrier
; surface over signals the body already computes).
;
; ── THE HEARTBEAT BODY  (runnable: device-heartbeat.fk · proven: tests/device-heartbeat-band.fk -> 127) ──
;   A heartbeat is a presence beacon: (device, organs, channels, beat). A peer that receives it learns
;   WHO is there (device), WHICH organs are live (hb-organ-active? — the observability read), WHICH
;   transports they share (hb-shared), the BEST channel to open (hb-best-channel, by priority), whether
;   they CAN connect (hb-can-connect?), and whether they are still ALIVE (hb-present? — a beat within
;   `stale` ticks; silence means the body went quiet, which is itself information). One heartbeat shape,
;   one discovery, channel-blind — the carrier is whatever is open.
;
; ── THE CHANNELS ARE CARRIERS — interchangeable ports behind the heartbeat ── [lane-sorted honestly]
;   wifi   — UDP broadcast / mDNS on the LAN.            [MEASURED — standard, what v0 of the app uses]
;   ble    — BluetoothLeAdvertiser (Android) / CoreBluetooth (Mac): advertise a beat, scan for peers.
;            No AP needed, device-to-device.             [BUILDABLE — platform carrier, not yet wired]
;   audio  — data over sound: speaker emits an FSK/chirp beat, mic decodes it (ggwave-style acoustic
;            networking). Low bandwidth, works across a room with no pairing. [BUILDABLE — real, niche carrier]
;   video  — screen shows a QR/anim beat, another device's camera reads it. One-way, line-of-sight,
;            needs no radio at all.                       [BUILDABLE — carrier]
;   The body never changes when a channel is added; a new transport is a new carrier emitting/decoding
;   the SAME heartbeat cell. core-abstraction-first: not four integrations, one beacon over a port.
;
; ── OBSERVABILITY — "see what it is doing, which organs, surprise, infer error" ── [carrier over built signals]
;   What to SHOW is mostly things the body already produces, surfaced by a thin live dashboard (a web
;   page the heartbeat + toolkit feed; one on the Mac, one in the app):
;     STATE / ORGANS ACTIVE — straight from the heartbeat: hb-organs / hb-organ-active? per device.
;     PRESENT PEERS — hb-present? over the received beacons (who is alive on the mesh right now).
;     SURPRISE EVENTS — already built: novelty.fk (a reading below the recognition floor) and
;       anomaly-band.fk (a value outside the seen band). A surprise is a recognition that did not fit.
;     INFER ERROR (core for learning) — already built: sequence-predictor/markov-2 PREDICT the next;
;       when the actual arrives, the mismatch (predicted != actual) is the prediction error, counted by
;       drift-detect.fk and graded by self-grounding-classifier.fk. That error is not a bug — it is the
;       learning signal (predict -> observe -> err -> update), the active-inference grain the whole
;       spine already rides. The dashboard makes it VISIBLE; the recipes already make it real.
;   So observability is a carrier (the live view); the things it shows are body, mostly already proven.
;
; ── HONEST LANES ──
;   SHIPPED — the heartbeat/discovery body (device-heartbeat.fk -> 127): organ-state, shared-channel
;     selection, liveness. The surprise + inference-error signals it would surface (novelty, anomaly-
;     band, drift-detect, self-grounding) are already proven three-way.
;   BUILDABLE — the per-channel carriers (wifi heartbeat first — the app already POSTs over wifi; then
;     BLE advertise/scan, audio FSK, video QR), and the live observability dashboard (Mac + app).
;   CARRIER-NEXT — wiring the heartbeat emit/decode into the app + the Mac witness server, and the
;     dashboard rendering state/organs/surprise/inference-error live.
;
; KIN: channel-interface.fk (the consent law per channel — a beat is witness, a connection is reach,
;   silence is whole) · resource-port.fk (each channel a typed port) · shared-sensing.form (the mesh
;   these heartbeats form) · cell-sync.fk (what flows once two devices connect) · novelty.form +
;   anomaly-band.form + drift-detect.form + self-grounding-perception.form (the surprise + inference-
;   error the dashboard shows) · recognition-router.form · lc-honest-lane.
;
; LINEAGE: shared-sensing.form proved many bodies sensing one field; this is how they FIND each other —
;   a beat on any open channel — and how a human SEES the mesh breathing: who is present, which organs
;   are live, what surprised the body, and how wrong its last prediction was (which is how it learns).
